<p><b>Luther Ronzoni Vandross</b> (April 20, 1951 – July 1, 2005) was an American <a href="Singer-songwriter" title="Singer-songwriter">singer-songwriter</a> and <a href="Record_producer" title="Record producer">record producer</a>. During his career, Vandross sold over twenty-five million albums<sup id="cite_ref-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-1"><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup> and won eight <a href="Grammy_Award" title="Grammy Award">Grammy Awards</a><sup id="cite_ref-2" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-2"><span>[</span>2<span>]</span></a></sup> including <a href="Grammy_Award_for_Best_Male_R&B_Vocal_Performance" title="Grammy Award for Best Male R&amp;B Vocal Performance">Best Male R&amp;B Vocal Performance</a> four times. He won four Grammy Awards in <a href="Grammy_Awards_of_2004" title="Grammy Awards of 2004" class="mw-redirect">2004</a> including the <a href="Grammy_Award_for_Song_of_the_Year" title="Grammy Award for Song of the Year">Grammy Award for Song of the Year</a> for the track "<a href="Dance_with_My_Father_(song)" title="Dance with My Father (song)">Dance with My Father</a>",<sup id="cite_ref-BBC_3-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-BBC-3"><span>[</span>3<span>]</span></a></sup> co-written with <a href="Richard_Marx" title="Richard Marx">Richard Marx</a>.</p>
<p>By popular vote, Luther Vandross was inducted into The SoulMusic Hall of Fame at <a href="../../w/index-title=SoulMusic.com&action=edit&redlink=1.php.html" class="new" title="SoulMusic.com (page does not exist)">SoulMusic.com</a> in December 2012.<sup id="cite_ref-4" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-4"><span>[</span>4<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
